newsitem.title: UK: NWE naphtha supported by Asia, pressured by crude.
newsitem.headline: NWE naphtha supported by Asia, pressured by crude.

text.p: NWE naphtha was steady to weaker on Thursday as crude oil prices fell, but strength in Asia underpinned the market, traders said.
June swaps were talked around $183/$184 before weaker crude pushed this down by around $1.50, traders said.

One dealer said that while few Russians were actively on offer there was some 20,000 tonnes in the hands of a trader. Small fob pieces were also thought available but these, too, were not widely shown to the market.
